HEADWORD: Trifarious
<hw>Tri*fa"ri*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>trifarius</ets> of three sorts or ways, threefold; cf. Gr. <?/. Cf.
<er>Bifarious</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Facing three ways;
arranged in three vertical ranks, as the leaves of veratrum.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

